    <note>Zhang(1) Rushi [11666] Treated as a lineage (third) nephew of Zhang(1) Quhua [185], who moved from Kaifeng, Suixian to Henan, Luoyang xian where Rushi was buried. Zi (Yaofu) and sons' mingzi ( Shanfu(3) [17732] has the same mingzi as a son of Zhang(1) Yaozuo, Shanfu(2) [13964]) both suggest their may be a kinship connection with Zhang(1) Guifei [3153] (later Huanghou), empress of Renzong), whose father, Yaofeng [13963], and uncle, Yaozuo [321], were both Henan residents. Ouyang Xiu, WJ, 24,7a-8b. CBD, 3, 2365.</note>
